
[1]behen

   BE'HEN, BEN, OR BEK'EN, n. A plant. The white behen is a species of
   Cucubalus, called Swedish Lychnis, or gum sepungar. The empalement of
   its flower resembles net-work, and its leaves have somewhat of the
   flavor of pease.

   The behen of the shops, or white behen, is spatling poppy. Red behen is
   sea lavender.
